  "source_id": "migraine",
  "name": "Migraine - Comprehensive Provider Query (DX + Meds)",
  "description": "Simulates a neurologist identifying their complete migraine patient population. Combines: migraine diagnosis codes (multiple subtypes) and triptan medications. No labs path — migraine has no defining laboratory marker. Tests Condition + MedicationRequest resource union for high-specificity drug class.",
  "prompt": "I need to identify my complete migraine patient population for a quality improvement initiative on triptan adherence. From clinical experience, migraine patients are documented in different ways: most have a formal migraine diagnosis (with or without aura, sometimes hemiplegic, occasionally just 'headache disorder'), and most are on triptan medications for acute attacks.\n\nPlease run multiple FHIR queries to capture the full population:\n1. Patients with any migraine diagnosis (parent migraine, with aura, without aura, hemiplegic, headache disorder)\n2. Patients prescribed triptans (sumatriptan, rizatriptan, eletriptan, zolmitriptan, naratriptan)\n\nFor each query, return the matching resources. I want the union of all patients found.",
